cs.FL, cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.CR, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with finite state automata and their computational power.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as the paper discusses verification power of the automata.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper investigates the computational power of the automata with bounded-error postselection and real-valued transitions.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of a prover in verifying some nonregular unary languages.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also less likely but possible as the paper deals with recognizing and verifying languages.
